Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with network performance monitoring and proposes a solution using programmable switches. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also a possible category as network performance monitoring is important for detecting security threats. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a new class of lean algorithms for performance monitoring. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with monitoring and controlling network performance. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with measuring and analyzing network performance metrics.
